<figureCitation box="[151,280,397,423]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 10−18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[292,364,397,423]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,812,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-277@7.[151,1435,812,1848]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 29 and 30, Mejdalania bia gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 31 and 32, M. longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 33 and 34, M. unciformis gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. Scale bars: 29–34 = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">31−32</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
