<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="113" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,469,495]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[561,644,469,495]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), subtriangular lateroapical process with dorsal rami robust and acute, directed caudally, ventral rami shorter and directed anteroventrally; subgenital plates, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1286,1367,505,531]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), subrectangular, with lateral margins almost parallel; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[828,957,541,567]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
) with apodemal processes longer than the shaft, slender for the entire length, shaft slender and strongly sinuous, S-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" box="[199,1175,613,640]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,453,613,639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[525,627,613,639]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 6.1. 
<typeStatus box="[821,919,614,640]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Paratype</typeStatus>
(male), 5.7−6.1 (n=3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,649,675]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body yellow (
<figureCitation box="[505,637,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,812,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-277@7.[151,1435,812,1848]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 29 and 30, Mejdalania bia gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 31 and 32, M. longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 33 and 34, M. unciformis gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. Scale bars: 29–34 = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 31–32</figureCitation>
), green in life. Face (
<figureCitation box="[881,964,649,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with frons mostly orange, dorsal margin yellow. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[370,454,685,711]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,812,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-277@7.[151,1435,812,1848]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 29 and 30, Mejdalania bia gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 31 and 32, M. longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 33 and 34, M. unciformis gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. Scale bars: 29–34 = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) yellow with three longitudinal light orange stripes, one median and two lateral. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[265,349,721,747]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,812,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-277@7.[151,1435,812,1848]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 29 and 30, Mejdalania bia gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 31 and 32, M. longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 33 and 34, M. unciformis gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. Scale bars: 29–34 = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) yellow, with orange basal angles. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[881,962,721,747]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) yellow semi-hyaline with a dark yellow longitudinal strip adjacent to the anal margin. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[737,818,757,783]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,812,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-277@7.[151,1435,812,1848]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Habitus, dorsal and lateral views, respectively. 29 and 30, Mejdalania bia gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 31 and 32, M. longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. 33 and 34, M. unciformis gen. et sp. nov., holotype male. Scale bars: 29–34 = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506294/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" box="[199,1182,793,820]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,793,819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">External morphology.</emphasis>
External morphological characters as in the generic description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,399,829,855]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[688,771,829,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), subtriangular, high in the basal half and narrowing in the apical half, approximately 1.7 times longer than high; anterior margin with well-developed lobe; ventrobasal and dorsoapical margins thickened, ventral margin rectilinear, dorsal margin strongly declivous apically; lateroapical process with dorsal rami robust and acute, directed caudally, shorter ventral rami directed anteroventrally; apex rounded; apex rounded. Subgenital plates, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[826,909,973,999]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with apical third slightly curved dorsally; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[306,388,1009,1035]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), subretangular, with lateral margins almost parallel. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1127,1209,1009,1036]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) approximately half length of the style. Style (
<figureCitation box="[440,568,1045,1072]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 15–16</figureCitation>
) with apophysis slightly curved dorsally. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1287,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
) with apodemal processes longer than the shaft, sinuous and slender for the entire length, apex rounded; shaft strongly sinuous, S-shaped, flattened dorsoventrally, slender for the entire length with smooth lateral margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" box="[199,633,1153,1179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,425,1153,1179]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Female terminalia.</emphasis>
Female unknown.
</paragraph>
