<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1333,1359]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name alludes to the long apodemal processes of aedeagus, exceeding the length of the shaft (
<figureCitation box="[221,304,1369,1395]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,469,1540]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1405,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves, 2021" authorityName="Gonçalves" authorityYear="2021" box="[322,521,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mejdalania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,521,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Mejdalania longa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[528,617,1405,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[528,617,1405,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves, 2021" authorityName="Gonçalves" authorityYear="2021" box="[742,899,1405,1431]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mejdalania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unciformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[742,899,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">M. unciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[905,995,1405,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[905,995,1405,1431]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the shape of the aedeagus. However, the subtriangular shape of the pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[596,678,1441,1467]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) and the long apodemal processes of aedeagus, exceeding the apex of the shaft (
<figureCitation box="[300,430,1477,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1830,1854]" captionTargetBox="[155,1420,209,1775]" captionTargetId="figure-15@5.[151,1435,181,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10–18. Mejdalania longa gen. et sp. nov., holotype male: 10, head, frontal view; 11, forewing; 12, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 13, valve and subgenital plates, lateral view; 14, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 15, connective and style, dorsal view; 16, style, lateral view; 17, aedeagus, lateral view; 18, aedeagus, caudal view. Scale bars: 10 = 1.0 mm, 11 = 2.0 mm, 12–18 = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5506286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5506286/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">Figs 17–18</figureCitation>
) are characteristics that easily differentiate 
<taxonomicName authority="Gonçalves, 2021" authorityName="Gonçalves" authorityYear="2021" box="[933,1037,1477,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mejdalania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[933,956,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[973,1037,1477,1503]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">longa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1046,1138,1477,1503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1046,1138,1477,1503]" pageId="4" pageNumber="113" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
